…unveils tournament kits The Authentic Nigeria football and Allied Sports Supporters Club will travel to Cameroon for the 2021 AFCON with over 500 supporters to cheer the Super Eagles to victory. President, ANFASSC, Abayomi Ogunjimi, said the supporters club would be in Garoua as the Eagles’ 12th player at the tournament. He also disclosed that the body had unveiled their official AFCON 2021 kit. The outfit, produced by a kit company in Nigeria, CONE, is designed to motivate Nigerians and Eagles, he added. “ANFASSC plans to travel to Cameroon with over 500 supporters to cheer our team to victory,” he told PUNCH Sports Extra. On the club’s new AFCON kits, he added, “The central design theme is an abstract logo of ANFASSC  inspired by the green and white colours of the Nigerian flag. “The design was enlivened to capture the energy of the 1994 Super Eagles team and ‘can do’ spirit of average Nigerians.” Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com